import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import pandas as pd

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    plt.hist(data['x'], bins=20, color='blue', alpha=0.5)
    plt.axvline(data['x'].mean(), color='red', linestyle='dashed', linewidth=1, label=f"Mean: {data['x'].mean():0.2f}")
    plt.axvline(data['x'].median(), color='green', linestyle='dashed', linewidth=1, label=f"Median: {data['x'].median():0.2f}")
    plt.xlabel('X')
    plt.ylabel('Frequency')
    plt.legend()
    plt.title('What is the distribution of X?', wrap=True)
    return plt

chart = plot(data)
```

import pandas as pd

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    data = data.dropna()
    plt.scatter(data['x'], data['y'], c=data['diff'], cmap='coolwarm')
    plt.colorbar(label='Difference')
    plt.xlabel('X')
    plt.ylabel('Y')
    plt.title('Is there a correlation between X and Y?')
    return plt

chart = plot(data)

import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import pandas as pd
import seaborn as sns

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    sns.set(style="whitegrid")
    fig, ax = plt.subplots(figsize=(8, 6))
    sns.boxplot(x="diff", data=data, ax=ax, color='skyblue')
    ax.axvline(data['diff'].min(), color='red', linestyle='--', label=f"Min: {data['diff'].min():0.2f}")
    ax.axvline(data['diff'].max(), color='green', linestyle='--', label=f"Max: {data['diff'].max():0.2f}")
    ax.axvline(data['diff'].median(), color='orange', linestyle='--', label=f"Median: {data['diff'].median():0.2f}")
    ax.axvline(data['diff'].quantile(0.25), color='purple', linestyle='--', label=f"Q1: {data['diff'].quantile(0.25):0.2f}")
    ax.axvline(data['diff'].quantile(0.75), color='brown', linestyle='--', label=f"Q3: {data['diff'].quantile(0.75):0.2f}")
    ax.set_xlabel('Diff')
    ax.set_ylabel('')
    ax.set_title('What is the range of values in Diff?')
    ax.legend()
    plt.tight_layout()
    return plt

chart = plot(data)
```

import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import pandas as pd

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    data['x'] = pd.to_numeric(data['x'])
    mean_x = data['x'].mean()
    fig, ax = plt.subplots()
    ax.axvline(mean_x, color='r', label=f'Mean X: {mean_x:.2f}')
    ax.legend()
    ax.set_xlabel('X')
    ax.set_ylabel('Count')
    ax.set_title('What is the average value of X?')
    ax.hist(data['x'], bins=20, color='b')
    return plt

chart = plot(data)
```

import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import pandas as pd

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    data['x'] = pd.to_datetime(data['x'], format='%H:%M:%S', errors='coerce')
    data = data[pd.notna(data['x'])]
    data = data.sort_values(by='x')
    plt.plot(data['x'], data['y'])
    plt.xlabel('X')
    plt.ylabel('Y')
    plt.title('How does the distribution of Y change with respect to X?')
    return plt

chart = plot(data)
